The program theory is not complete. We must also understand why people drive fast. We have not included the theory of causation from drivers‚Äô perspectives. Suppose, for instructional purposes, Figure 3 represents the most common DAG that explains why drivers speed. Therefore, why was he or she driving fast? To make a meeting. Why was this meeting important? To win a contract? Why was this contract important? (unemployment?)
